The next Biennial should involve four hundred local, state, and international artists, including Manfred Kamm, Pia Camille, Wilfredo Pelias, and Yoko Ono, and will take place at the Museum of Modern Art in New York from March 21 to March 24, 2020, at the Beacon Arts Center in Salem, Massachusetts.


The Museum of Art has released the first photos from the upcoming exhibition “ONE PHASE.” The forty-fourth edition of the annual event, titled “ONE STEP BACK,” will open in March 2021. The exhibition will include works by eighty-six artists from thirty-five countries and territories. The list of participating artists is as follows:  Austrian Albrecht Dürer;

Czech artist Michał Soskala;

Polish artist Grzegorz Kawczak;

Peruvian artist Rodrigo Palma Torres;

Korean artist Park Joo; and

Korean-born American artist Sam Haley. The show will also present work by artists such as Han Ho Yoon, Lin-Manuel Miranda, and Linda Satterwhite, among others
